# WHOIS Lookup

## What is WHOIS?

WHOIS is a protocol used to get information about a domain name or IP address.

It helps identify:

* Domain owner
* Registrar
* Registration date
* Expiry date
* Name servers
* Contact information (sometimes hidden)

---

# Why WHOIS is Useful in Cybersecurity

WHOIS is used during:

* Reconnaissance
* Bug bounty hunting
* OSINT investigations
* Domain analysis
* Threat intelligence

Security researchers use it to gather public information about targets.

---

# Install WHOIS

## Linux

```bash
sudo apt install whois
```

## macOS

```bash
brew install whois
```

---

# Basic WHOIS Lookup

```bash
whois google.com
```

This returns domain information about Google.

---

# Example Output

```text
Domain Name: GOOGLE.COM
Registrar: MarkMonitor Inc.
Creation Date: 1997-09-15
Expiry Date: 2028-09-14
Name Server: NS1.GOOGLE.COM
```

---

# Useful WHOIS Commands

## Lookup a Domain

```bash
whois example.com
```

## Lookup an IP Address

```bash
whois 8.8.8.8
```

## Save Output to File

```bash
whois example.com > result.txt
```

---

# Important Fields

| Field         | Meaning                     |
| ------------- | --------------------------- |
| Registrar     | Company managing the domain |
| Creation Date | When domain was registered  |
| Expiry Date   | Domain expiration           |
| Name Servers  | DNS servers used            |
| Org Name      | Organization owning domain  |

---

# Cybersecurity Use Cases

## 1. Domain Investigation

Check suspicious domains.

```bash
whois suspicious-site.com
```

---

## 2. Identify Hosting Provider

WHOIS on IP addresses may reveal hosting providers.

```bash
whois 1.1.1.1
```

---

## 3. Detect Recently Registered Domains

New domains are often used in phishing attacks.

Look at:

```text
Creation Date
```

---

# Limitations

* Many domains use privacy protection
* Some information may be hidden
* Not always accurate

